\begin_layout Abstract
A 
\emph on
big-data
\emph default
 text-mining analysis detects prominent themes in the business-strategy
 literature.
 A 
\emph on
Latent Dirichlet Allocation
\emph default
 (LDA) model is applied to a corpus comprised of journal-article titles
 and abstracts from eight journals spanning the period 1980 – 2020.
 This corpus consists of around 5,500 documents containing an aggregate
 of 1.25 million words.
 Five prominent business-strategy themes are identified 
\emph on
a priori
\emph default
.
 The LDA model based on the aforementioned corpus is applied to eight articles
 known to coincide with the dominant themes.
 These known-theme documents are found to correspond to distinct topics
 inferred by the model.
 Substantial overlap exists, making thematic discrimination challenging.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Abstract
Subsequent work for the INFORMS Annual Meeting will seek to improve the
 thematic-discriminant power of the approach.
 This includes expanding the corpus size to include full-text articles.
 More-sophisticated modeling will attempt to pull in additional grammatical
 information.
 Also, the LDA approach will extended in order to expressly bridge between
 LDA-inferred topics and 
\emph on
a-priori-specified
\emph default
 themes.
 The intended result seeks to demonstrate a concept of operations for literature
 research potentially useful for academic researchers and business consultants.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section*
Introduction.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Advances in statistical methods for text-mining — variously referred to
 as 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

big
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 data, text analytics, natural-language processing, 
\emph on
etc
\emph default
 — offer new ways to perform literature search.
 Statistical algorithms sift through expansive collections of text in document
 or message format.
 The applications include topic detection, document classification, and
 trending 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Srivastava2009"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Such methods have in recent years assumed an increasingly prominent role
 in academic research.
 Blei and Lafferty provided an early demonstration of their potential to
 group scientific texts by topic 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Blei2009"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Antons2019"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 extended this work, attempting to infer scientific impact.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Schmiedel2019"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 performed a methodological demonstration of big-data tools for research
 in organizational culture.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Tay2018"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 studied visualization approaches to interpreting topic-analysis results.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Liu2019"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 conducted a thematic survey of the business-ethics literature.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Torabi2019"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 tried to discriminate between 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

fake
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 news and factual reporting.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Brooks2018"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 performed a critical comparison of topic analysis with more-conventional
 methods for discourse studies using UK National Health System content.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We describe here a 
\emph on
topic-analysis
\emph default
 study of the business-strategy literature.
 Detecting specific major themes in the literature is our goal.
 This intent coincides closely with that of 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Blei2009"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Liu2019"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
 We look for five distinct themes that appear prominently in business-strategy
 research during the last half-century.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We employ a method called 
\emph on
Latent Dirichlet Allocation
\emph default
 (LDA), commonly used for topic analysis.
 LDA attempts to group documents by 
\emph on
topic
\emph default
.
 It is an 
\emph on
unsupervised-learning
\emph default
 method in that it does not depend on exogenous, 
\emph on
a-priori
\emph default
 assignment of documents to topic classes.
 Such algorithms probabilistically estimates the strength of association
 between each document and each topic based on statistical similarities
 in their texts.
 LDA was first described by 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Blei2003"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
After training our LDA model, we examine its handling of documents known
 to preponderantly address our 
\emph on
a-priori
\emph default
-identified themes.
 Subsequent work extends the approach in an attempt to produce a more-robust
 thematic classifier.
 These extensions are inspired by 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Xie2013"
literal "false"

\end_inset

, but do not explicitly reproduce its approach.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section*
Target audience.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
At least three constituencies may find this work particularly interesting.
 Academic researchers represent the first.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Schmiedel2019"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 explicitly seeks to demonstrate the utility of topic analysis as a 
\emph on
strategy for inquiry
\emph default
.
 Topic analysis bins documents from a corpus into topically coherent latent
 topic groups.
 This aides in the localization of research content associated with a theme
 of interest.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Business consultants are the second potential beneficiaries of topic analysis.
 Automation of text classification can reduce their barrier to accessing
 the breadth and depth of academic research related to their practice.
 Innovative ideas with potential to advance consulting practices become
 more-easily discoverable.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Thirdly, text-mining practitioners may take note of an apparently-novel
 approach to processing.
 Inspired by 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Xie2013"
literal "false"

\end_inset

, this work extends the original method of 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Blei2003"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
 We focus here on the distinction between 
\emph on
Latent Topics
\emph default
 inferred by LDA modeling and 
\emph on
Themes
\emph default
, in which researchers and consultants actually take interest.
 This work moves towards an 
\emph on
adaptive
\emph default
, Bayesian-Learning approach 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Jihan2018"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 to document classification according to research themes.
 This might support a use case for interactive literature search, in which
 a model 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

learns
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 thematic associations based on LDA topic allocations and other machine-learning
 outputs.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
At its present state of maturity, topic analysis by no means obviates the
 need for traditional research.
 It could be used to compile a preliminary bibliography for a research project.
 Human 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

touch labor
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 remains to ascertain which documents in a topical class are useful and
 which are not.
 Identification of potentially-related work that might not have otherwise
 occurred to a researcher is the primary benefit.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Branded as 
\emph on
artificial intelligence
\emph default
, the abilities text-mining methods such as topic analysis are sometimes
 overestimated.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Vladawsky-Berger2020"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 emphasizes that these methods fundamentally are specialized applications
 of statistics.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Waters2016"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Davenport2018"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 contain cautionary tales about overestimating their capabilities.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section*
Summary of thematic study.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
Business-strategy corpus.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We assemble a textual 
\emph on
corpus
\emph default
 of business-strategy articles published in the period 1980 – 2020.
 Preliminary results illustrated here are based on titles and abstracts.
 The corpus for the annual-meeting presentation will be based on full-text
 articles.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Fourteen academic journals, most of which are focused primarily on business
 strategy, were considered.
 Details are listed in 
\begin_inset CommandInset href
LatexCommand href
name "[Hamlett2020]"
target "https://github.com/hamlett-neil-ur/BizStratTopicAnalysis"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
 Of these, eight were determined to be useful and practical.
 The summary table in 
\begin_inset CommandInset href
LatexCommand href
name "[Hamlett2020]"
target "https://github.com/hamlett-neil-ur/BizStratTopicAnalysis"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 provides the rationale for and document count for each.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The resulting corpus contains approximately 5,500 documents — article titles
 and abstracts — in all.
 Each document is processed through a text-manipulation process called 
\emph on
annotation
\emph default
 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
after "Chapter 2"
key "Weiss2010"
literal "false"

\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "JSLabs"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
 This involves cleaning up the text and discarding non-information-bearing
 words like prepositions, conjunctions, and articles.
 Consecutive words are also combined so that key phrases remain intact.
 When all of this is done, this corpus contains more than 1.275 million distinct
 terms, or 
\emph on
tokens
\emph default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
Dominant themes in business strategy.
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "subsec:DominantThemes"

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We seek to detect five dominant themes in our corpus.
 Figure 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "DominantThemes"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 summarizes these themes.
 Four of these themes have occupied central positions in the business-strategy
 conversation during the last 50 years.
 The fifth theme — information as a differentiating asset — is still emerging.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Business strategy focused on operational efficiency beginning in the late-ninete
enth century.
 Frederick Winslow Taylor pioneered the field of 
\emph on
Scientific Management
\emph default
.
 Relentless pursuit of industrial efficiency was his focus.
 Although much of Taylor's actual work fell into disrepute, its underlying
 hypothesis retained credibility.
 A 
\emph on
Management-Science
\emph default
 discipline focused on industrial efficiency became the staple of graduate
 schools of business throughout the academy 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Stewart2009"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Kiechel2012"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 describes a 
\emph on
Management Century
\emph default
, during which these ideas dominated.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In the late 1970s, Harvard Business-School professor Michael Porter observed
 that price alone does not unequivocally explain marketplace success 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Porter1979,Porter1990,Porter1996"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
 He asserted to the effect that 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

The race is not to the swift, nor the battle to the strong
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

, necessarily.
 Were price the dominant determinant, the 
\emph on
Bertrand Model
\emph default
 of competition would prevail, and many markets would tend to states of
 unprofitability 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
after "Chap 12"
key "Pindyck2017"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Porter's 
\emph on
Competitive-Advantage
\emph default
 framework
\emph on
 
\emph default
recognized that firms can differentiate on factors other than price.
 His framework also explains industry structure and balances of power between
 buyers and sellers.
 It views combinations of positioning and resources as the key 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Martin2015"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
 Porter's framework is fundamentally grounded in bedrock concepts from microecon
omics.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Clayton Christensen, one of Porter's students, noticed in the 1990s that
 industry structures can shift surprisingly and quickly.
 Dominant firms' positions based on product distinction can suddenly be
 upended by lower-price substitutes.
 This phenomenon is referred to as 
\emph on
Disruptive Innovation
\emph default
 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Christensen2015"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
 Christensen's framework shares with Porter's an emphasis on positioning
 and resources.
\end_layout

