\begin_layout Standard
Figure 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "Known-theme allocations"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 contains illustrative results from applying the known-theme documents from
 Figure 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "Known-theme docs"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 to an LDA model.
 This model assumes 
\begin_inset Formula $K=10$
\end_inset

 latent-topic classes and uses a dictionary size of 
\begin_inset Formula $L=450$
\end_inset

 terms.
 A heat-map depiction is used because LDA does not unequivocally assign
 each document to a distinct topic.
 For each 
\begin_inset Formula $\textrm{Document}_{n}$
\end_inset

 it produces a set of conditional probabilities 
\begin_inset Formula $\Bigl\{ Pr\bigl(\textrm{Topic}_{\kappa}\mid\textrm{Document}_{n}\bigr),\quad\kappa=1,\cdots,K\Bigr\}$
\end_inset

.
 These are conditional probabilities, so as usual,
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\sum_{\kappa=1}^{K}Pr\bigl(\textrm{Topic}_{\kappa}\mid\textrm{Document}_{n}\bigr)=1\textrm{.}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Float figure
wide true
sideways false
status open

